# Python Dependencies — Use uv

Always use [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) for Python environments and packages. Do not use `pip`, `python -m venv`, or `pipx` unless uv cannot do the job.

## Virtual environments

```bash
# ❌ BAD: python3 -m venv .venv
# ✅ GOOD:
uv venv
source .venv/bin/activate   # or: uv run <cmd> without activating
```

## Installing dependencies

```bash
# ❌ BAD: pip install pre-commit
# ✅ GOOD — ad-hoc / dotfiles tooling:
uv pip install pre-commit

# ✅ GOOD — pyproject.toml projects:
uv add requests
```

## Running tools

```bash
# ❌ BAD: pipx run pre-commit
# ✅ GOOD:
uv run pre-commit run --all-files
```

## Syncing from requirements

```bash
# ❌ BAD: pip install -r requirements.txt
# ✅ GOOD:
uv pip sync requirements.txt
```

When updating dev setup (e.g. `AGENTS.md` pre-commit), show uv commands. Use `uv pip install` for one-off tools; use `uv add` / `uv sync` when the repo has a `pyproject.toml`.
